- und Ratskollegien formierten und um eine Transformation eher unverbindlicher Beratungsfunktionen zu quasi parlamentarischen Rechten bemühten. Einschlägige verfassungsgeschichtliche Dokumente von der Benediktsregel aus dem 6. Jahrhundert bis hin zu bischöflichen und päpstlichen Wahlkapitulationen aus dem 15. Jahrhundert werden hinsichtlich ihrer kulturgeschichtlichen Zusammenhänge und Wirkungen analysiert.  aIn the medieval Christian church the claim to authority possessed by abbots, bishops, and popes stood in contrast to the rights of consultation held by monks, canons, and cardinals. This work demonstrates how the latter formed themselves into more or less independent electoral and consultative colleges.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAuthorityvReligious aspectsvChristianityvHistory of doctrinesvMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aAuthorityxReligious aspectsxChristianityxHistory of doctrinesyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aChurch historyvMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aChurch historyyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aChurch polityvHistoryvTo 1500. 0aChurch polityxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aRELIGIONvChristian TheologyvEcclesiology. 4aKirchengeschichte. 4aKirchenpolitik. 4aMittelalter. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Western.2bisacsh  aMiddle Ages.  aecclesiastical history.  aecclesiastical politics.1 aKrüger, Thomas M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET GESCHICHTE, POLITIKWISS., SOZIOLOGIE  2013z9783110317114oZDB-23-DPS0 cprintz978311027725840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311027737140